hat, and then I had hidden a - a box with a few cigarettes in somewhere, gone out for a walk on Sunday afternoon and came back and - my father wasn't a smoker but - he says, well what about lending - giving him a cigarette. I knew that - there was trouble
. But - I can't remember - I - I think he just he gave me a telling a off and that at was it and I didn't smoke again 'til I was - twenty-six. Then I started borrowing from him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 He'd taken it up by then had he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 He had started smoking about forty 
- the age of forty-one. Yes. I think he was forty-one when he started smoking. By that time cigarettes were coming more popular, after the war you see. And he would stock them in the shop and he - oh he was never real}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13126017\charrsid16660515 ly a heavy smoker, he didn't in}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 hale con
sciously certainly, and - then - with his work when I - I became older and he had a motor vehicle, he never learned to drive, and I used to take him round for part of his work and probably stop at the school - for a while he inside with the men he was int
erviewing and - I used to read and I used to just ask him for a cigarette and then - I became a bit choosy and I - start}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13126017\charrsid16660515 ed buying my own and of course g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 one from bad for - from bad to worse ever since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Can you tell me what your parents brought you up to
 consider important in life? Were they the sort of parents who talked about values much and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Well - I don't think there was any preaching. We were given to understand that you weren't to steal, the commandments were to be observed 
and - and all the rest of it, it would be a case that you were brought up with this - more - inculcated you know and - I can't remember there was any - any preaching like that at all consciously. But probably certainly as mentioned swearing and this we - 
that this was something we didn't do, others might do it but we weren't allowed to do it and - and we didn't feel the need for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 What about your behaviour towards your parents, how did they expect you to behave towards them when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 
Oh well you were - I don't think this presented really a problem from our other - you grew up with - so many people round about of course - the others - the other family, the - my uncle and aunt being up at the other end of the house and you're moving bac
k and forward between the two places - you - you - probably learnt as much in one end as you did in the other end you see. And you were - gradually becoming aware of the values of - good behaviour, possibly my aunt you know - next door was - more - she - 
s
he was more genteel you see, they came from Edinburgh, she would have her own values you see and probably didn't approve of some of the things we had. So I would have become conscious of - others restrictions besides the - the more traditional ones - thro
ugh her. But - difficult to pinpoint you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Did you ever argue with your father for example over a matter of opinion or politics or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Well, later on, oh yes, yes, oh yes, oh yes, oh later on I - I would have had - an argument
 with him on - but - oh possibly not as a teenager so much. But later on - sometimes, not that we - either of us ever got very involved in politics but he would - he would be interested from possibly from - somebody he knew personally, that kind of thing.
 
I became aware of Labour policies, I became of the shortcomings of Tory governments and - things like that. Abuses, but I - I never really got involved myself - terribly and - that phase passed very quickly and in my local government service - I - partici
p
ated at all. I - I couldn't, I - I felt - I shouldn't and I didn't. And - in my matters - my time - with the Education Department was very useful when there were a general election declared, a candidate or an agent would come in to arrange about meetings,
 
and - it was very very good to be able to speak on - to all of them on the same footing, I mean they came the whole lot of them in the office for that matter and - settled on a campaign about - dovetailing their meetings and seeing that there was no clash
es. That kind of thing, that's - that's very essential. Mm hm. Very useful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Did your father favour any particular party when you were a child do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Well - not so far back as that, no, but the first elections I remember would be the - p
ost-war elections. I think he - he had a great - fancy for Lloyd George I think, and - I think probably he would have favoured - Lloyd George - fact}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13126017\charrsid16660515 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 on of the - of the Liberals. We had a bit of - controversy then because - one of these elections in the ear
ly '20's we - we landed with a candidate from both camps you see. Stornoway - well I think -, there was a man Mackenzie Livingstone - and a man T.B. Wilson Ramsey, and the local Liberal party adopted Mackenzie Livingstone and Ramsey - didn't - came on lat
er and he became an MP for - for - Western Isles and - he - he was the better of the two that way, and Mackenzie Livingstone, I don't think he was a terribly effective MP. But - Wilson Ramsey seemed to have been very very - good type.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Was your father an easy person to talk to, an approachable sort of father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 
Yes. Yes. Oh yes, we - in later life it was - we were very friendly, in that way, you know, because we had some kindred interest, I - by this time of course I'd got involved - in local governm
ent and I would be interested in - on along similar - similar lines, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Could you confide in your mother when you were a small boy, if you had any little worries or problems?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Would you be more inclined to talk to her than your father about that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 She was more approachable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Can you remember if they felt it was right or wrong to hit back if attacked by another child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 No. Ah well - I - I - I jus
t can't remember this one. No, I should imagine it would depend on how they would be prepared to get the - objective you know of the situation, decide for themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Was there much - do you remember incidents of bullying or children fighting each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 
Yes. Oh yes, oh yes, was plenty going on at school of course. Oh yes. Not so much on a - on a - on a personal basis, there - there were - were the occasional - bust up with somebody but for no - somebody's - you know - some trouble maker starting
 - starting to be - make - insult somebody and then get somebody else to do the fighting, that - that kind of thing. A bit of - there were two villages you see in the school, Brue and Barras, and - oh I remember a - a big fight when I was a very small boy
. They - they used to have a battle with stones - throwing stones at each other, you know. But I don't think there was any -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Did the girls take part too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 I think there was one girl on the other side - who did - she - she was fairly a great champi
on, otherwise I - I don't know if she took part in the stone throwing but, my goodness, she could - look after herself and look after some of the boys too. But - normally the boys were - the girls were very - genteel, they never - interfered - this one, s
he was a strong lassie, and - in fact she became a great person, a very charming person in later life, and a very fine singer. And she went off to - Canada.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 What did you do on a Sunday when you were a child, you mentioned Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 We went to Sunday school in the afternoon usually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Was Sunday strictly kept?
