the eats were the - the - the main source of interest in our very young days. And then - New Year time - rather - hectic time with - young - young neighbours coming in - having a \{BLANK\}
 and them moving on somewhere else. And then when we were quite small 
children - we used to go round the neighbours and wish them a happy New Year and then you get a lump of turf and maybe a penny and that kind of thing, or a piece of cake, a piece of shortcake you know, that - that kind of thing.
