d
rews University and I was going to stay - with an uncle who was a schoolmaster and lived just six miles from - St Andrews. But - this knocked it on the head and I had to give it - opt for a provisional training there, so - I was in hospital for a year, an
d
 then I went back and I - convalesced for - quite a while, but - helped my father you know, clerical - with clerical work and - I - got my first official appointment unpaid as assistant Registrar, but - then we acquired a van for the - shop, about 1928, a
n
d I drove the van and helped in the shop and helped in the office - 'til about 1934. And then there was a sudden demand for somebody - with the kind of - knowledge I had in Stornoway at short notice. And I was probably the only - person in the island to h
