ve the requisite - knowledge and I just came in on a temporary basis, and then eventually - just got my appointment was confirmed, the man I was replacing never came back, and - from then on - I started then as - assistant - Public Assistant Of - Public A
s
sistance Officer, Assistant Registrar, collector of rates and all the rest of these local government posts, with a man - George McLeod, who had been - in the post himself first, Inspector of Poor, Clerk of the Poor Parish Council and - held several - jobs
 of that - local government jobs, a very very able man, and - then I stayed with them and - succeeded him in 1946, he took ill in 1945, I acted in his absence for a year, then I was appointed to succeed him in 1946, and - then there were the paid \{BLANK
\} in
 the social services - National Health Service, National Assistance, National Insurance, and I wasn't very sure - just where I was going to land at that point, and - being in the Public Assistance Service, we all the opportunity of applying for posts in t
