d I will complete my service with them next Thursday. Yes. So - in a way things - didn't go right at the - school leaving stage but - I've no regrets just the same. I would have liked to have had university experience of having gone to university but as f
a
r as career is concerned I felt I had a worthwhile career, and - I also felt that - with what the options were - very restricted - was - in those days you became provisionally, you became a teacher, a minister - or a doctor, and looking back I don't think
 
I would have enjoyed being any one of them. I don't think so, I - I first thought I might - probably, whatever it was, destiny, fate, lot, call it what you will, that - I fell into something that was far more suited to the talent I had. So to that extent 
it's been - quite a satisfying life. I might have had more remunerative employment in Civil Service - or in a profession but - on the other hand - I was thankful to be able to do - a reasonable job.
