 which was fairly near us - the manse was fairly near us, I - he was a bachelor, and his housekeeper was a great friend of my mother's. And - oh I think there must have been - possibly - two maids in the manse at the time looking after this old man, along
 
with the - the housekeeper, there were one maid anyway. And they seem to have had a very free and easy time and the - the - the - people round the village were welcomed in as visitors. I think it was probably to make - the situation fairly easy for the - 
the peop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16523904\charrsid16660515 le}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 
 - staff, and they must have - they had games of all kinds. I'm not sure if they had cards but they certainly had - things like - say marbles you know or Chinese Chequers. That kind of thing. Aye. And - chess, I got a beautiful set of chessmen and
 I didn't know what it was and it must have disappeared before I began to realize what they were. When they were left you see, when he left and he flitted about 1912, and I got a lot of odds and ends like this. Aye.
