, I don't remember - there were - there were some ex - we had some excellent draughts players in the village. There were one neighbour of ours in particular - he was - he was very good, and - he was - captured at - Antwerp in 1914. He was a prisoner of wa
r
 in Germany. And there was an army officer in the same camp with him who must have been an expert, and whatever gaps there were in his knowledge, he - he filled them in for him, and he was really a first rate draughts player and - oh we had quite a few go
od draughts players, I had another uncle myself who was very good. So this was something they took a great interest in. Some - some of them really became very good at it, I - I never take a - took a great interest in them.
