t the same - movement of population today, but in my young days - the - we used to have a lot of people - my mother's peop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16523904\charrsid16660515 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 
e used to come from Back and they used to walk across the moors and that's quite a distance from Back to Barras, and - my two aunts a
nd their husbands and - other relatives would come along, and sometimes we had to - we would put up quite a number of them, maybe half a dozen, even more sometimes. And - this was fairly commonplace at that time, and then on a - certain day you might have
 a very large number for a dinner - at dinnertime, lunchtime. Yes, I have seen - on occasion, it was an exceptional situation, where including the family we had thirty-six for lunch on a Sunday, and everybody got their lunch.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 How did you manage it, did you have different sittings?
