Yes, well what it was, the - the - the more regular visitors we had - had to turn to and become waiters for the - the strangers. It was just - it was - a - a - a very - exceptional situation - where a group of people cam
e from a village - where they didn't use - where they used to have the communions at the same time as Barras, and for some reason or other, some quirk in the calendar or something else, this occasion they didn't have their communions, and we had two minis
t
ers in the church on that occasion - who were very attractive to these people, they had their own minister actually, and another man who belonged to the area that was a minister in Skye or somewhere, and - I had an uncle here in Stornoway who was an elder
 
in the church and he and I happened to be at the door and this van drew up at the door, and the drivers came out - out and he spoke to my - and we both knew them - we both knew the driver, and he told us his problem that he had a - a van load of people wh
o
 were complete strangers in the place, they'd never been before, he just didn't know what to do with them. And my uncle very politely said, oh bring them in here, there's enough here for them all. And somehow or other my mother found a - found the - where
 with all to feed the lot. And that was it. Yes
