 get around very much of course and - but - people weren't - people kept themselves to their - you know, always different characters and - people who kept themselves to themselves and - it was more - differences of that kind than - than any - yes, differe
n
ces of personality rather than - any conscious feeling of - class distinction or like that I think. Yes. There were peo - poor people possibly who felt their poverty very keenly and - you know - maybe they weren't terribly well dressed and that kind of th
ing and would have been - rather self-conscious about that kind of thing. There - there was a great deal of poverty of course in these early days. Yes.
