\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Oh yes, well some - lady with gracious manners, this kind of thing, kind to people, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 But you think it was a concept rather imported into the community?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Oh yes. Oh yes, yes oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Your home belonged to your father didn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Yes. Oh yes, he - he bought the place and built the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 You mentioned later he got a croft, was that after he bought the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 
Yes. Yes. He got that as a result of - a family emigrating to Canada. A family in the neighbourhood not very far away from us, just about - a hundred yards down the road from us. He bought the croft from them you see, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Was that when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 
Oh I was quite young, it would be - just - around 1912 I should imagine, I would be around seven or eight years, you know, about 1912 I expect. And this family emigrated to Canada, and - he bought the croft. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16523904\charrsid16660515 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 uilt the byre on it you see, and then - later on we built the shed for the cart and the gig and then it became a garage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Is that what it still is?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Well, it was my - my brother has built a garage just alongside the house recently. Just finished recently, a garage - down on
 the croft up 'til then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet, presumably not in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 No, I - I - I know - he had difficult times, my father had - I know he had difficult times -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Before the end of the war, in that period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 
I can't remember exactly, it could have been - perhaps - during the war or - sometime after it. I think he had a bit of difficulty there - and the first - you see, there was a great deal of - of credit given. You see, peo
ple went away to the fishing, they would have no money - the girls in the family go away to the fishing, they're - perhaps the - men of the household had to go to the fishing on the east coast, and there'd be no money 'til they come back you see. Now if t
h
ey hit a bad patch - they just couldn't pay - the bills, and then he had to carry the can, he might have to tide them over for - maybe another season. But generally people were very honest, and even if it went on for a year, they would still - make the ef
f
ort. So - he would have carried a fair amount of - credit for - periods, and it could be that he - he might have had - to - get an overdraft or even get somebody else to guarantee an overdraft for him. But I'm not terribly sure a - about this, it's rather
 far back. But I had a feeling at - at one time - some problem like this. Yes. But he - seemed to have got over it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 The work he took on, being Registrar of births and public assistance work and that sort of thing, was that done do you think mainly for 
money or mainly for the interest of the work, or both?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Oh I think it was mainly - to supplement his income. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 But would you have said the main income came from the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Oh yes. Oh yes, because all these jobs were part time in themselves, none of them - mounted up to - a full time post, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 
Do you ever remember the custom of rough music, people being made to leave a community by banging and clattering of tin kettles outside their door?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 No. No, we never had any of that, none of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Did anybody teach you anything in the way of school work before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 
Oh I couldn't remember that. Possibly, my father may very well have - done some work but I don't know, probably they would have been interested to s
ee whether you were intelligent or not you see. But I don't remember any attempts - no, I can't remember, I can't even remember just exactly when I went to school. The only thing I do know - and yet I'm not conscious of this of course but I was naturally 
l
eft handed. And I probably started to write left handed and I was stopped. And this was done - in those days, in most places. And - I had to develop - a right hand - the right hand writer and I had quite a lot of trouble in school - I remember I used to g
e
t into trouble but I became quite a reasonable writer, and - lots of people used to compliment me on my writing - when I became a registrar particularly, and that it was quite good, copper - copperplate, it wasn't all that good, my - my father was excepti
onally good. He really had a copperplate hand, and his books were - a thing of joy - beautiful - work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 But you didn't start stammering or anything as a result of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 No. No, I don't remember that I had any problem like that, but - evidently I h
ad to give it up, and the - the schoolmaster mind you later on he maintained that if he had known about it, I wouldn't have - I would have been allowed to carry on, but this is hindsight you see, by - you know, as the years developed I became more accepta
ble - and - psychology and all the rest of it was being - advancing and - people felt it was wrong to stop people from doing these things. And of course nowadays it's - nobody - worries unduly, and I came across contemporaries in Stornoway who were left}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16523904\charrsid16660515  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 handed and had - had been allowed to continue. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 You say you're not sure what age you started school, do you think it would have been about five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Oh it would have been about five, yes, oh yes, so far as that - aye - goes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Did you go in the morning and afternoon from the start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 
Oh yes. Oh of course in those days everybody went at the same time and came home at the same time. And I'm sure with us it would have been - wise - to let us stay on 'til the older ones came home, we had a - we 
had a long distance to walk you see, we had over a mile to go, and endeavoured to be in company with the rest of the - children from the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 And you had your dinner at home did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Oh you had a meal - your meal at home. You would have - pr
obably carried something - a piece or something, and - on occasion I used to come with - relatives - who were nearer school and could come home - to lunch, sometimes I - I went up with them and got a - little of what was going, might be - just some cold p
orridge from the morning or something like that, they weren't terribly well off but - I quite enjoyed it, with plenty of milk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 When you first went to school can you remember who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 I can't remember so much but I can guess pretty well. I can remember the people who were next, well in the houses and round about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 You'd go off in a little group would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Oh yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Did your mother take you up do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 No, I shouldn't think - I should think my father took me. Yes. She had plenty to do at home and he would have been -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Because there'd have already been two or three young ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Oh yes, yes, oh yes, there would have three at least - that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 What kind of school was that at that time, would that have been a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 
Oh well - it was a - a - a school board school it was - still - what - what they would call today - what we call today a public school you know, supported by - by the local authority, well the school board was the local autho
rity for schools in those days, based on the parish you see. Yes. I think there was just the one big room then if I remember rightly, I think there were two teachers, I - I think it was just the two - headmaster and one assistant teacher, and I think it w
a
s one big room, but later on it was divided and - then it became three rooms I believe, three separate rooms. With three teachers, yes. And at the time I left school there was a hundred and twenty children in the school, since then its come down to sixty 
o
r thereabouts, and there's between sixty and seventy nowadays. Anyway that was away back 1919, there were a hundred and twenty on the role at that time, and it would have been possibly higher before the war - first war, before 1914. They would have reache
d it about -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 About 1911 it was at its peak?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Most of - most of the schools here were at the peak just shortly before the first world war, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8863920 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 What did you think of school, that school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3561112 JM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 Oh - well I think I - generally I liked it very m
uch. Yes, I - I liked the schoolmaster. And I think this first lady we had that she was rather fond of the belt. But - then there were or two since then who were like that, but - I was a reasonably diligent worker and - I didn't get into too much trouble.
 
And - some of them - very good indeed. But - I had a great respect for the schoolmaster, we had - during the - greater part of life in school. Then - it was only a year before I left school that - he left to get a better job, and - we had another man who 
was more of the traditional domineering type came in and I was only with him for a year, a very very nice man but - I don't think he was a - an exceptional teacher.
