d there must have been - as one result of the war a shortage of male teachers. And it wasn't until about 1923 that - the young men who had come back from the war - were completing their training and coming into the schools - as teachers you see. And from 
that time onwards the staffing situation would have eased. And - certainly the last three years of my life at school were very good from that point of view, I think we had splendid teachers. Yes.
