ondary department really got under way. And they had a - a very remarkable man who came in at that point, and he was - he replaced the headmaster, he actually came in as a science master, but they actually - he replaced the headmaster, and it was he, a ma
n, Mr W.J. Gibson, and he - really put the Nicholson on its feet. And from that - onwards they - he went - he went on now, he retired in the year - the year I left school, at the - after I left school, 1925.
