No. I don't think we had anything special. At that time. No. There was so much you see - once you were able to do any work - you know you were expected to help getting the water in, getting the peats in and all the rest of it, 
there wasn't a great deal of time for - for hobbies, we - we devised our own, I can remember we used to - play as being soldiers during the war, you see, being down at - to the farm at night - making - guns of bits of timber and this kind of thing. But - 
I don't think there was anything in the way of - organized hobbies or - anything like that.
