ibly 1918 I think about the last year of the war so it probably would have been - but the market went on - the market day went on quite a long time after that, it was - became a - was just a great island festival, people came to the town and there was - s
i
deshows and things like that out on the old market stands, and people came to the town just for the sake of - coming to town and the place would be very busy, and then - you used to have - it was - out where the county hospital is there, and a great carry
 
on with gigs full out with people and then later on car - when the cars and the buses came in they used to do this so it must have gone on right into the 1920's but - by that time I don't think there was very much in the way of buying and selling of stock
