\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5316270\charrsid16660515 led more and they camped out in the villages on the - fringes of the villages you see, and they would go round the village mending tins and making - tin pails
 for us for the milking - and - and - they used to make small tin lamps for use down in the byres, you know, a - a lamp with no - globe on it you see, just a - a small open - conical kind of lamp with a little - wick in it and - jugs and pails and odds an
d ends like that and if you had an old pail that was leaking they would mend it for you, that kind of thing, but - I think these skills are pretty well died out now.
